turns.speaker: M
turns.content: I just got a letter I have to go back.

turns.speaker: M
turns.content: I don't understand, I don't underst--

turns.speaker: F
turns.content: They said you're home for at least four years.

turns.speaker: M
turns.content: I guess they can do it,

turns.speaker: M
turns.content: The National Guard is I guess really spread thin and then everyone has to go.  We all have to go back, my whole companies going back.

turns.speaker: M
turns.content: I can't believe it. I just got back.

turns.speaker: M
turns.content: I just got I feel like I'm in shock actually.

turns.speaker: F
turns.content: I don't even know what to tell you.

turns.speaker: M
turns.content: I guess you're just going to have to have it without me.

turns.speaker: M
turns.content: Hey listen, it's going to be okay though, all right?

turns.speaker: F
turns.content: Me?  I'm not worried about me.

turns.speaker: M
turns.content: I'm going to be fine too, okay?

turns.speaker: M
turns.content: I know I have a good... I have a really good group of guys with me.

turns.speaker: F
turns.content: You're going with the same ones?

turns.speaker: M
turns.content: Do promise me you're going to take a lot of pictures.

turns.speaker: M
turns.content: I just wish there was something I could do.

turns.speaker: F
turns.content: Mm hmm.  We'll build a bunker and never come out.

turns.speaker: M
turns.content: I really don't want to go, I don't want to go...

turns.speaker: F
turns.content: I'll send you a letter every single day.
